race.comment: SAVAMOON (3) is free running and was swamped late on the Hillside last time but missed a nose there prior as a $2.7F and that reads well. He will use the inside gate and that should benefit around here. Pozman's 3kg claim brings him right into it. PULA (10) resumed on the Hillside over 1300m and just missed when expected to need it. Proven second-up and she will appreciate the step up to 1500m. Rates to go close with average luck in the run. VEYEPEE (8) led over 1440m and belted the Geelong Maidens by 2.8L on debut. He'd had a stack of jumpouts and is a progressive type in a top barn. No surprise if he takes the next step. DELTA SKY (9) spiked her numbers beaten 2L at Pakenham over 1400m. It was a big effort after being back and wide. Maps well and sits down in the weights. She's won 4/5 over this distance and keep safe. SUPREME SOVEREIGN (1) resumes and is a UK import having his first run for the Waller yard. Lane rides and he goes fresh. A betting watch.
